comment: I‚Äôm a Potter fan, the books, and the films. I liked the first installment of Beasts, but I was most excited about Depp stepping in as this wonderful villain. I like the 2nd, Beast too, but mostly because we got to see far more of Depp as Grindlewald. He really did the part so flawlessly, and he looked fantastic! Now I will not bother with anymore of these films, and without Depp, all interest is lost. Of course I believe Depp, and as a survivor of domestic abuse, I feel safe in saying that I don‚Äôt believe he ever raised a hand to her. Sure, it definitely looks like they had a toxic relationship, and neither was good for each other, but that doesn‚Äôt mean Depp is a wife beater, and nothing that I‚Äôve seen thus far proves anything that Jackal has said, quite the opposite actually. Heard reminds me  far more of my abuser than a ‚Äúsister survivor‚Äù. That‚Äôs just my honest reaction to all of the evidence, the recordings, and the court transcripts. Nd I actually believed her in the beginning. Yet frankly, unless I hear that an actor is harming children, I could care less what they do in there private lives. I like films, not celebrities . I think WB made a huge mistake. I didn‚Äôt even know who Heard was until she began this fiasco, and I didn‚Äôt even know that Depp had left his last girl. I just don‚Äôt pay attention. Heard does not have a lot of star power. Honestly, they could put any beautiful woman in her role, and it won‚Äôt make a lot of difference, but replacing a true talent like Depp can destroy a film. I won‚Äôt be seeing either WB film, or any film from WB. I think their work practices are heinous. I won‚Äôt be seeing any new Pirate films going forward without Depp either, and I can‚Äôt believe Disney would even bother.  The film industry is struggling enough. I cannot fathom why they would govern themselves in this way. I thought they liked money.

comment: People will see Aquaman 2. Probably not in such big numbers as saw the first one, but they'll still go if Amber Heard is in the cast or not. More would go if she wasn't, as there wouldn't be any negative buzz, even if the film is just ''okay'. But people will go, it will still make money.  However, people absolutely, positively, will not go and see a 'Pirates' film without Captain Sparrow. It will just seem like a cash-grab tribute act. Like 'the Mask 2' or 'Blues Brothers 2000' or the 'Ghostbusters' remake. To be honest, the brand had become tired anyway. Like Terminator and MIB and Transformers, it doesn't matter what you do, it's the law of diminishing returns in action. It won't make a billion again but, with Captain Sparrow,  it might have still made 6 or 7 hundred million worldwide. Without him, it will be 330 million worldwide, tops, so it will lose money after marketing. That's just a fact. Fantastic Beasts is in trouble. JK Rowling has alienated the woke crowd. Warners have now alienated the anti-woke crowd. Anybody who doesn't feel that it is essential viewing will just be turned-off by all the negative publicity it will receive from the partisans that filters into the mainstream through osmosis. The last film wasn't well-received. The next part already doesn't seem essential. The problem is that they're all being led by Marketing departments that think 'clicks' translates to bums on seats, and it doesn't when those clicks aren't actually just about the film (tv series, whatever) itself. People are 'interested' in seeing a car crash, but nobody wants to be sat in the back seat for one.

comment:
The movie is called "AQUAMAN" not "MERA".  

If nearly 2 million online petitioners didn't move HBO to re-do season 8 of Game of Thrones with different showrunners.  And, Game of Thrones is HBO's biggest Cash Cow that generated over $3 Billion in Net profits for HBO, what makes you think WarnerBros is going to cave in?

The only way Amber Heard is not on Aquaman 2 is if Amber Heard has contractual issues with WarnerBros.  Nothing else.

Petitions may have had real teeth back in the 1970s when they called on the network to bring back the Bionic Woman after they killed her off in the Six Million Dollar Man.  People were really attached to her character, such as, young girls, kids who were hospitalized and adults who just fell in love with Jamie Summers(Bionic Woman).

If WarnerBros gives in, that would be setting a precedent, such that, Hollywood will not be able to create a film/tv show without having it go through a committee of millions of people.  That does not make sense.  You will have a million different ideas of where a show/film should go.

Don't be like Disney.  Disney painted themselves in a corner when they decided to be only family friendly.  Disney made their bed.  They have to lie in it.  So, of course they will hire and fire based on the room temperature of the fans.  WarnerBros is not all family friendly.  Netflix is not all family friendly.

Be who you are and stick to it. And, stop throwing your friends, family and actors under the bus if they find themselves in some trouble because "FANS" won't like to see them in your film.  That's stupid.  That's how great talent gets lost and goes missing.

You can't satisfy everybody.
